The paper deals with a Bayesian framework for solving the sparse non-negative least squares problem, which involves signal and support recovery. This problem is commonly studied in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
